{{Other people2|Frank Hughes (disambiguation)}} {{BLP sources|date=February 2010}} {{Infobox person | name = Frank John Hughes | birthname = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1967|11|11}} | birth_place = [[The Bronx, New York]], [[United States|U.S.]] | occupation = Actor | years_active = 1990–present }}
'''Frank John Hughes''' (born November 11, 1967) is an [[United States|American]] [[film]] and [[television]] [[actor]] best known for his portrayal of [[William Guarnere|"Wild Bill" Guarnere]] in the [[HBO]] miniseries ''[[Band of Brothers (TV miniseries)|Band of Brothers]]'', Tom Fox in ''[[Catch Me If You Can]]'', Tim Woods in ''[[24 (TV series)|24]]'', and [[Walden_Belfiore#Walden_Belfiore|Walden Belfiore]] in ''[[The Sopranos]]''.<ref>{{cite news |title=TV Review: 'Sopranos' trails off with a tease |first=Rob |last=Owen |url=http://www.post-gazette.com/stories/ae/tv/tv-review-sopranos-trails-off-with-a-tease-488812/#ixzz2FbNwxry1 |newspaper=[[Pittsburgh Post-Gazette]] |date=10 June 2007 |accessdate=20 December 2012}}</ref>
==Early life and career== A native of the [[South Bronx]], Hughes studied jazz composition at the [[Berklee College of Music]] in [[Boston, Massachusetts|Boston]]. At the age of nineteen he became one of the youngest members ever to be given lifetime membership in [[The Actor's Studio]]. He also studied with acting teacher Sonia Moore. After numerous stage productions [[Off-Broadway]], Hughes made his feature film debut in [[Robert Celestino]]'s ''True Convictions'' (1991).
Since then he has starred in such films as: ''[[Bad Boys (1995 film)|Bad Boys]]'' (1995) opposite [[Will Smith]], ''Lonely in America'' (1991), ''[[The Funeral (1996 film)|The Funeral]]'' (1996) opposite [[Benicio del Toro]] and [[Christopher Walken]], ''Layin' Low'' (1996), ''[[Mr. Vincent]]'' (1997) (for which he won mass critical acclaim at the [[Sundance Film Festival]] for his role as John Vincent), ''Urban Jungle'' (1999), ''Robbers'' (2000), ''[[Anacardium (film)|Anacardium]]'' (2001) (for which he won BEST ACTOR at the New York Independent Film Festival), and [[Steven Spielberg]]'s ''[[Catch Me If You Can]]'' (2002). He also appeared in Robert Celestino's ''Yonkers Joe'' opposite [[Chazz Palminteri]] and [[Christine Lahti]] and in [[Jon Avnet]]'s ''[[Righteous Kill]]'' opposite [[Robert De Niro]] and [[Al Pacino]].
==Television== Hughes is a veteran of television. He had recurring roles in the series: * [[HBO]]'s ''[[The Sopranos]]'' as [[Walden Belfiore]], a soldier in the [[Soprano crime family]], who committed the last murder in the series when he killed [[Lupertazzi crime family]] boss, [[Phil Leotardo]]. * HBO's mini-series, ''[[Band of Brothers (TV miniseries)|Band of Brothers]]'' (2001) as "[[William Guarnere|"Wild Bill" Guarnere]] * The [[Dick Wolf]] series ''[[Players (1997 TV series)|Players]]'' (1997) * [[NBC]]'s series ''[[LAX (TV series)|LAX]]''
Other appearances include: ''[[Cover Me: Based on the True Life of an FBI Family|Cover Me]]'', ''[[Law & Order]]'', ''[[Homicide: Life on the Street]]'', ''[[Feds]]'', ''[[Without a Trace]]'', ''[[Monk (TV series)|Monk]]'', ''[[Boomtown (2002 TV series)|Boomtown]]'', ''[[Kings of South Beach]]'', ''[[Curb Your Enthusiasm]]'', ''[[JAG (TV series)|JAG]]'', ''[[The Path to 9/11]]'', ''[[Law & Order: Criminal Intent]]'', ''[[NCIS (TV series)|NCIS]]'', and ''[[Criminal Minds]]''.
==Video game work== * He provides voiceovers in the video game ''[[Call of Duty 2: Big Red One]]''.{{cn|date=November 2012}}
==Latest works== In 2009, Hughes joined the cast of the series ''[[24 (TV series)|24]]'' as Secretary of Homeland Security, Tim Woods. He returned to that role in 2010. ==References== {{Reflist}} ==External links== * {{IMDb name|400606|Frank John Hughes}} * {{ymovies name|1800396979}}
